The Zig Standard Library also contains functions to compare Slices , strings, and more. See the rest of the `std.testing` namespace in the Zig Standard Library for more available functions. ### Test Tool Documentation §

`zig test` has a few command line parameters which affect the compilation. See `zig test --help` for a full list. ## Variables §

A variable is a unit of Memory storage. It is generally preferable to use `const` rather than `var` when declaring a variable. This causes less work for both
humans and computers to do when reading code, and creates more optimization opportunities. Variables are never allowed to shadow Identifiers from an outer scope. The `extern` keyword or @extern builtin function can be used to link against a variable that is exported
from another object. The `export` keyword or @export builtin function
can be used to make a variable available to other objects at link time.
