### C Translation Caching §

The C translation feature (whether used via `zig translate-c` or `@cImport` ) integrates with the Zig caching system. Subsequent runs with
the same source file, target, and cflags will use the cache instead of repeatedly translating
the same code. To see where the cached files are stored when compiling code that uses `@cImport` ,
use the `--verbose-cimport` flag:

verbose\_cimport\_flag.zig

```
 ... 
