## Single Threaded Builds §

Zig has a compile option `-fsingle-threaded` which has the following effects:

* All Thread Local Variables are treated as regular Container Level Variables . * The overhead of Async Functions becomes equivalent to function call overhead. * The `@import ( "builtin" ).single_threaded` becomes `true` and therefore various userland APIs which read this variable become more efficient. For example `std.Mutex` becomes
  an empty data structure and all of its functions become no-ops. ## Illegal Behavior §

